%S A316192 0,0,1,3,4,22,69,418,2210,14024,89075,597581,4076855,28499301,
%T A316192 202464580,1460982297
%N A316192 Number of self-avoiding polygons with perimeter n and sides = 1 that have vertex angles from the set 0, +-Pi/6, +-*Pi/3, +-Pi/2, +-2*Pi/3, +-5*Pi/6, not counting rotations and reflections as distinct.
%C A316192 Holes are excluded, i.e., the boundary path may nowhere touch or intersect itself.
%C A316192 From _Anton Pirogov_, Jun 21 2026: (Start)
%C A316192 Also number of free simple matchstick polygons with perimeter n on the cyclotomic ring Z[zeta_12].
%C A316192 The values a(11)-a(16) were determined by enumeration with the tilezz library using exact cyclotomic integer arithmetic over Z[zeta_12]. (End)
%H A316192 Contest Organizers, <a href="http://www.recmath.org/contest/Snakes/index.php">Al Zimmermann's Programming Contests - Snakes on a Plane</a>, Fall 2006.
%H A316192 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="http://www.randomwalk.de/sequences/a316192.htm">Illustration of polygons of perimeter <= 8</a>.
%H A316192 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz">tilezz</a> - exact cyclotomic geometry library including a polygon enumerator.
%H A316192 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://ratdb.app.pirogov.de">Rat Explorer</a> - interactive database of cyclotomic matchstick polygons.
%H A316192 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz-ratdb">RatDB datasets</a> - reproducible datasets containing the enumerated polygons.
